eu.cqse.check.clike

Class ConditionalStatementsEqualCheck

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.cqse.check.framework.core.CheckImplementationBase
      • eu.cqse.check.clike.CLikeConditionalBlockCheckBase
        • eu.cqse.check.clike.ConditionalStatementsEqualCheck

  • @ACheck(name="Statements in Conditional Expression are equal",
        description="Statements inside the body of `if, else, else-if` or `switch/case` constructs should not be the same, because it introduces unnecessary duplicated code. A way to deal with equal statements in conditional expressions is to merge the condition and keep the body once.\n\n``` js \n// The following piece of code:\n   if (condition1) { \n     foo(); \n   } else if (condition2) { \n     foo(); \n   } else { \n     bar(); \n   } \n\n// can be rewritten as: \n   if (condition1 || condition2) { \n     foo(); \n   } else { \n     bar(); \n   }\n```",
        languages={JAVA,CS,CPP,OPEN_CL,JAVASCRIPT,XTEND,SWIFT,GROOVY,GOSU,KOTLIN,OBJECTIVE_C},
        parameters=ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE,
        groupName="Bad practice",
        defaultEnablement=YELLOW)
public class ConditionalStatementsEqualCheck
extends CLikeConditionalBlockCheckBase
    Check for equal statements inside conditional expressions. The statements inside conditional expressions are checked if they consist of the same statements. Conditional expressions checked are: if/else/else if and switch/case constructs.
